Managing a company as an introverted creative entrepreneur very attached to privacy should not be complicated, and yet, that's sometimes the case. Most online resources and coaches tell you to work with the big (and sinister) technology companies using extraverted techniques. Advertise here, follow the algorithm, share who you are. Have your service checked, be available 24/7, 7 days a week, answer questions with a video of yourself, respond immediately. Video, video, video.
March 1, 2024
It's a year of transition for me.
I do not want to feed my money, data, and energy to the big technology companies. Nor do I want coaches who have only one extraverted solution that they apply to everyone. I am exploring new ways to manage my activity while fighting against the idea I believed for a long time, that success requires doing things a certain way.
Wish me luck!
I have already taken the first steps.
I left Facebook, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and deleted my private WhatsApp account.
I also removed the last external tracker, Google Analytics, from my website yesterday, and it feels good.
I recently subscribed to a European-based CRM for better GDPR compliance, and I will transfer my activity over the coming weeks.
I transferred my MX record to Proton and now fully benefit from SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, without having to pay Google for basic email address validation.
March 3, 2024
